                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d777</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">777</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-11-06T13:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-11-06T13:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-06T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="777" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-06T13:00:00-05:00">November 6, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4327. French Emb has already taken up with Dept questions mentioned in ur 5746
                    Nov 5, 5 p. m. Dept did not give any definite answers in respect courses of
                    action such contingencies. For ur info Dept has not yet received from Nanking
                    its report discussion there but Emb has now been instructed supply account of
                    meeting and its views.<note n="5" xml:id="d777fn5">Telegram No. 1558, November
                        6, 1 p. m., to the Ambassador in China, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
